    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In Nahua society, persons belonging to the noble class who performed state functions and ruled the macehualtin, or common people.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000096648/Getty Research Institute [online] (1997-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000096762/Chávez and Klatt, Mexico: A Brief History (2006)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000096637/Lockhart, The Nahuas after the Conquest (1992)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Personen in de Nahua-maatschappij die behoorden tot de adellijke klasse die staatsfuncties bekleedden en heersten over de 'macehualtin', de gewone mensen.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>En la sociedad nahua, las personas pertenecientes a la clase noble que desempeñaban funciones de estado y gobernaban el macehualtin, o gente común.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ipan sociedad nahua, macehualmeh nobles tlen quipiyayah ce tlanahuatilli ipan estado huan tlanahuatiyayah ica macehualmeh, zo gentes tlen quence cenca.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
